The paper deals with real-time occlusion handling in outdoor mixed reality systems, which involves computer vision, graphics, and robotics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves graphics and rendering techniques, which falls under cs.GR (Computer Graphics). The use of optical flow for depth estimation and foreground probability map calculation suggests the involvement of robotics and autonomous systems, which falls under cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also involves machine learning techniques for semantic segmentation, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the use of visibility-based rendering method suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
